												<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Grumbuk-Dev wrote:<BR>I was the person who said I'd follow up on the DoT agro/hate (and coded /melody, fwiw). We had to change the way PBAE DoT's worked a while ago to prevent exploits, and one unfortunate side effect of the change was that hate generation from DoT's was affected. Basically, damage is a key source of how much NPCs will hate a player, and without the damage being applied, less hate is created. We tried a few things, but were met with various problems and then more pressing issues came up and this was left behind. I'll try to get some progress on this one soon. <BR><BR>Regards,<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>Yes, I remember Grumbuk, but at the time of writing the post it was easier the way I did it, rather than have to search a thread you posted to in order to be able to spell your name. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0></P>
<P>"For what it's worth" - Let's see what it is worth.... per just some of the aspects I posted in the previous thread&nbsp; it shows lots of items on the list.&nbsp; The only items that got fixed were very game breaking issues, like the epic 1.5 bugs ( which is still present but not constant), and Fading Memories, which was broken during the Disciplines System Alteration.&nbsp; Otherwise not one thing from the original list has been fixed, as I don't count the more over all items with modifiers as these were only added to new zones and expansions, not any added to pre-existing expansions, therefore a patch fix, not a real fix.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The list was posted back in July, without any items from it touched.&nbsp; Now we are rapidly approaching patch day, where finally, one item at least that we know about from the list is being patched.&nbsp; So at least from my point of view, what it is worth is a lot.&nbsp; It is the very first real item addressed from the original list for over five months.&nbsp; And it is being addressed solely because you decided to fart around on your own time and wound up creating the code, with the additional ability to test the fizzle rates, another major issue item from the original list.&nbsp; Personally I may never use it, as I'm so used to twisting that even when grouped with a second bard, I wind up twisting four songs anyway.</P>
<P>As far as the dot issue, Grumbuk said that the dots, not the pbae dots were also affected.&nbsp; However, I'm not sure that is totally accurate Grumbuk.&nbsp; The agro on chants were altered during the AA alteration, and it was felt it was an erroneous effect of the beastlord's agro alteration on their dots, lowering the generated hate for them.&nbsp; It happened prior to the AoE alteration.</P>
<P>Additionally, is there any way to get the AoE nerf altered?&nbsp; In its present state, bards can't join AoE groups at all.&nbsp; Plus, on raids, only one bard can AoE.&nbsp; Can the coding be changed so that no damage is taken if the mobs are trying to move towards the bard instead of just trying to move?&nbsp; This means it directly affects the AoE issues it was meant to address, yet allows for low level farming as well as AoE groups.&nbsp; Plus, having the stacking issues fixed so more than one bard can participate during raids would be helpful.</P>
<P>Polara</P>
																		
